    "data": "\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    Importance of Ziyarat-e-Ashura\nThe virtues and merits of Ziyarat Ashura can be best understood based on the Traditions of the Holy Infalliables (a.s.) which have been narrated regarding its importance and recitation. There are many incidents by which the importance of this Ziyarat is realized . \nThe Ziyarat is followed by 2 rakaats namaaz and a dua known as Dua-e-Alqamah which Imam Sadiq (a.s.) used to recite after Ziyarat-e-Ashura and he also taught the same to his companion Alqamah (r.a.).\nZiyarat-e-Ashura: In the light of traditions\nThe importance and merits of reciting Ziyarat Ashura can be understood from the following traditions:\nTradition 1\nAlqamah bin Mohammed ibn Hazrami (r.a.) narrates ‘I requested Imam Baqir (a.s.) to teach me a dua that I should recite on the day of Aashura after the reciting the Ziyarat of Imam Husain (a.s.) - from near his (a.s.) grave or from a distance.’ Imam (a.s.) replied\n‘O Alqamah, whenever you wish to recite the Ziyarat of Imam Husain (a.s.), you first perform two units of prayers. Then turn towards the grave of Imam Husain (a.s.) and while pointing towards it, you first say ‘Salam’ and then ‘Takbir’. Thereafter, you recite this Ziyarat (Ziyarate Aashura). If you do so, then as if you have recited the supplication read by the angels while visiting the grave of Imam Husain (a.s.). Moreover, when you recite this Ziyarat, then\n(a)\tAllah will record a million good deeds for you, erase a million sins and add a hundred million ranks to your rank.\n(b)\tYou will be included among those people who were martyred along with Imam Husain (a.s.) and you will share their ranks.\n(c)\tOn the day of Judgment, you will be included among the martyrs\n(d)\tYou will get the reward of all the Prophets, Messengers and all the people who have visited the grave of Imam Husain (a.s.) from the day that he (a.s.) was martyred till date.\nAnd the way of reciting the Ziyarat is like this…’\n(Then Imam (a.s.) recited the entire Ziyarat-e-Ashura for Alqamah (r.a.))\n(Kaamil al-Ziyarat, Ibn Qoolwayh, Ch. 71, p.194)\nAt the end of this tradition, Imam Baqir (a.s.) says:\n‘O Alqamah, if you can, then recite this Ziyarat every day send salutations to Imam Husain (a.s.). You will get all the rewards (of the one who recites it on the day of Aashura).’\nTradition 2\nImam Sadiq (a.s.) informs,\n‘The one who does the Ziyarat of Imam Husain (a.s.) on the day of Ashura, then paradise is obligatory upon him.’\n(Behaar al-Anwaar, vol. 101, p.104)\nZiyarat-e-Ashura: Hadith-e-Qudsi\nThe greatest merit for this Ziyarat is that it is the ‘Word of Allah’ (Hadith-e-Qudsi). Safwan (r.a.) narrates that Hazrat Jibraeel (a.s.) conveyed this Ziyarat to Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) on divine command and it has reached Imam Baqir (a.s.) through his noble ancestors.\nZiyarat-e-Ashura: Emphasis of Imam-e-Zamana (a.t.f.s.)\nThe emperor of the era, the chief of the universe, Imam-e-Zamana (a.t.f.s.) has stressed the importance of reciting Ziyarat-e-Ashura.\nShaykh Mohaddis Noori (r.a.) in his book “Najmus Saqib” writes that there was a person called Syed Ahmed Rashty who was on his way to Hajj with his companions.\nIt was winter and one night there was snow and ice accompanied by strong winds. \nSyed Ahmed got separated from his companions. \nHe says he was trembling with fear and cold as it was a place where people often looted.  Suddenly he saw a person with a shovel freeing the tree branches which were burdened with snow. The man greeted Syed Ahmed saying “Assalamu Alaykum Syed Ahmed! Where are you going?” Amazed at the person knowing his name he said he was on his way to Hajj but had lost his way.  The man told him “Alayka bin Nafela! Nafela! Nafela!” Syed Ahmed prayed his Maghrib and Isha salaah finishing each with its Nafela.  He saw the man again who asked him, “Have you not gone yet?” Syed Ahmed replied “No!” The man said, “Alayka bil Jameah! Jameah! Jameah!”\nSyed Ahmed says that I did not know Ziyarat-e-Jameah by heart but that day I could recite it as though I had memorised it. The man told him, “Alayka bil Ashura! Ashura! Ashura!”\nSyed Ahmed recited Ziyarat-e-Ashura and Dua Alqamah. The man then mounted on his horse and took him to his caravan and the companions he had been separated from.\nAs he parted Imam (a.t.f.s.) said to Syed Ahmed, “REMEMBER ZIYARAT-E-ASHURA, THERE IS NO GREATER GIFT THAN IT.” \nWe see how Imam-e-Zamana (a.t.f.s.) helped Syed Ahmed and stressed upon the recitation of Ziyarat-e-Ashura. It also points to the fact that Imam-e-Zamana (a.t.f.s.) desires that his followers should always remember the tribulations of his grandfather Imam Husain (a.s.) and they should always be aggrieved and anguished by the events of Karbala.\nWe pray to Allah – the Almighty – that He includes us among the fortunate ones – those who have the taufeeq of reciting Ziyarat-e-Ashura regularly.\nZIYARAT-E-ASHURA\nبِسْمِ اللهِ الرَّحْمٰنِ الرَّحِیْمِ\nBISMIL LAAHIR RAHMAANIR RAHEEM\nIn the name of Allah, the Beneficent, the Merciful.\nاَلسَّلَامُ عَلَیْكَ یَا اَبَا عَبْدِ اﷲ\nASSALAAMO A’LAYKA YAA ABAA A’BDIL LAAHE \nPeace be on you, O Abu Abdillah.\nاَلسَّلَامُ عَلَیْكَ یَا ابْنَ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ\nASSALAAMO A’ALAYKA YABNA RASOOLIL LAAHE \nPeace be on you, O son of the Messenger of Allah.\nاَلسَّلَامُ عَلَیْكَ یَابْنَ اَمِیْرِ الْمُؤْمِنِیْنَ\nASSALAAMO A’LAYKA YABNA AMEERIL MOMENEENA \nPeace be on you, O son of the Commander of the Faithful \nوَ ابْنَ سَیِّدِ الْوَصِیِّیْنَ\nWABNA SAYYEDIL WASIYYEENA \nand the son of the chief of the successors.\nاَلسَّلَامُ عَلَیْكَ یَابْنَ فَاطِمَۃَ سَیِّدَۃِ نِسَآءِ الْعَالَمِیْنَ\nASSALAAMO A’LAYKA YABNA FAATEMAATA SAYYEDATE NESAAAIL A’ALAMEENA \nPeace be on you, O son of Fatima, the chief of the women of the worlds.\nاَلسَّلَامُ عَلَیْكَ یَا خِیَرَۃَ اللهِ وَابْنَ خِیَرَتِہٖ \nASSALAAMO A’LAYKA YAA KHEYARATAL LAAHE WABNA KHEYARATEHI \nSalutation on you O the good creation of Allah and the son of His best creation!\nاَلسَّلَامُ عَلَیْكَ یَا ثَارَ اللهِ وَابْنَ ثاَرِہٖ وَ الْوِتْرَ الْمَوْتُوْرَ\nASSALAAMO A’LAYKA YAA SAARAL LAAHE WABNA SAAREHI WAL WITRAL MAWTOORA \nPeace be on you, O fearless warrior of Allah, the son of His fearless warrior, the one who was alone, and wronged by the murder of relatives. \nاَلسَّلَامُ عَلَیْكَ وَ عَلَی الْأَرْوَاحِ الَّتِیْ حَلَّتْ بِفِنَآئِكَ\nASSALAAMO A’LAYKA WA A’LAL ARWAAHIL LATEE HALLAT BE FENAA-EKA \nPeace be on you, and on the souls who died with you.\nعَلَیْکُمْ مِنِّی جَمِیْعًا سَلَامُ اللہِ اَبَدًا\nA’LAYKUM MINNEE JAMEE-A’N SALAAMUL LAAHE ABADAM \nI send peace of AIlah on all of you forever, \nمَا بَقِیْتُ وَ بَقِیَ اللَّیْلُ وَ النَّہَارُ\nMAA BAQEETO WA BAQEYAL LAYLO WAN NAHAARO \nso long as I remain alive, and the night and day remains.\nیَا اَبَا عَبْدِ اللهِ\nYAA ABAA A’BDIL LAAHE \nO Abu Abdillah, \nلَقَدْ عَظُمَتِ الرَّزِیَّۃُ وَ جَلَّتْ وَ عَظُمَتِ الْمُصِیْبَۃُ بِكَ عَلَیْنَا\nLAQAD A’ZOMATIR RAZIYYATO WA JALLAT WA A’ZOMATIL MOSEEBATO BEKA A’LAYNAA \ngreat is the loss, and unbearable and great is your tragedy for us,\nوَ عَلی جَمِیْعِ اَهْلِ اْلاِسْلَامِ\nWA A’LAA JAMEE-E’ AHLIL ISLAAME \nand for all the people of Islam,\nوَ جَلَّتْ وَ عَظُمَتْ مُصِیْبَتُكَ فِیْ السَّموَاتِ عَلی جَمِیْعِ اَهْلِ السَّمَاوَاتِ\nWA JALLAT WA A’ZOMAT MOSEEBATOKA FIS SAMAAWAATE A’LAA JAMEE-E’ AHLIS SAMAAWAATE \nand unbearable and great is your tragedy in the heavens, and for all the dwellers of the heavens.\nفَلَعَنَ اللهُ اُمَّۃً اَسَّسَتْ اَسَاسَ الظُّلْمِ وَ الْجَوْرِ عَلَیْکُمْ اَهْلَ الْبَیْتِ\nFA-LA-A’NAL LAAHO UMMATAN ASSASAT ASAASAZ ZULME WAL JAWRE A’LAYKUM AHLAL BAYTE \nMay Allah curse the people who laid the basis of oppression, and the wrongs done against you, people of the House\nوَ لَعَنَ اللهُ اُمَّۃً دَفَعَتْکُمْ عَنْ مَقَامِکُمْ\nWA LA-A’NAL LAAHO UMMATAN DAFA-A’TKUM A’N MOQAAMEKUM \nMay Allah curse who tried to obscure and deny your office and status,\nوَ اَزَالَتْکُمْ عَنْ مَرَاتِبِکُمُ الَّتِیْ رَتَّبَکُمُ اللهُ فِیْہَا\nWA AZAALATKUM A’N MARAATEBOKOMUL LATEE RATTABAKOMUL LAAHO FEEHAA \nwillfully neglected your rank and class Allah had made known in clear terms.\nوَ لَعَنَ اللهُ اُمَّۃً قَتَلَتْکُمْ\nWA LA-A’NAL LAAHO UMMATAN QATALATKUM \nMay Allah curse the people who killed you, \nوَ لَعَنَ اللهُ الْمُمَہِّدِیْنَ لَہُمْ\nWA LA-A’NAL LAAHUL MOMAH-HEDEENA LAHUM \nand those who made it easy for them, \nبِالتَّمْکِیْنِ مِنْ قِتَالِکُمْ\nBIT-TAMKEENE MIN QETAALEKUM \nby preparing the grounds for your killing.\nبَرِئْتُ اِلَی اللهِ وَ اِلَیْکُمْ مِنْہُمْ\nBAREA-TO ELAL LAAHE WA ELAYKUM MINHUM \nI turn to you and Allah, away from them,\nوَ مِنْ اَشْیَاعِہِمْ وَ اَتْبَاعِہِمْ وَ اَوْلِیَآئِہِمْ\nWA MIN ASHYAA-E’HIM WA ATBAA-E’HIM WA AWLEYAAEHIM \nand their adherents, their followers, and their friends.\nیَا اَبَا عَبْدِ اللهِ\nYAA ABAA A’BDIL LAAHE \nO Abu Abdillah,\nاِنِّیْ سِلْمٌ لِمَنْ سَالَمَکُمْ\nINNEE SILMUN LEMAN SAALAMAKUM \nI am at peace with those who make peace with you,\nوَ حَرْبٌ لِمَنْ حَارَبَکُمْ اِلی یَوْمِ الْقِیَامَۃِ\nWA HARBUN LEMAN HAARABAKUM ELAA YAWMIL QEYAAMATE \nAnd I am at war with those who make war with you, till the Day of Judgement.\nوَ لَعَنَ اللهُ آلَ زِیَادٍ وَ آلَ مَرْوَانَ\nWA LA-A’NAL LAAHO AALA ZEYAADIN WA AALA MARWAANA \nAnd may Allah cruse the family of Ziyaad and the family of Marwaan; \nوَ لَعَنَ اللهُ بَنِیْ اُمَیَّۃَ قَاطِبَۃً\nWA LA-A’NAL LAAHO BANEE UMAYYATA QAATEBATAN \nAnd may Allah curse the group and the tribe of Umiyyah, one and all, altogether;\nوَ لَعَنَ اللهُ ابْنَ مَرْجَانَۃَ\nWA LA-A’NAL LAAHUBNA MARJAANATA \nAnd may Allah cruse Ibne Marjanah \nوَ لَعَنَ اللهُ عُمَرَبْنَ سَعْدٍ\nWA LA-A’NAL LAAHO O’MARABNA SAA’DIN \nAnd may Allah curse Umar ibne Sa`ad, \nوَ لَعَنَ اللهُ شِمْرًا\nWA LA-A’NAL LAAHO SHIMRAN \nand may Allah curse Shimr\nوَ لَعَنَ اللهُ اُمَّۃً اَسْرَجَتْ وَ اَلْجَمَتْ وَ تَنَقَّبَتْ لِقِتَالِكَ\nWA LA-A’NAL LAAHO UMMATAN ASRAJAT WA ALJAMAT WA TANAQQABAT LE-QETAALEKA \nAnd may Allah curse the people who, carried out, saw, and were silent at, your killing\nبِاَبِیْ اَنْتَ وَ اُمِّی لَقَدْ عَظُمَ مُصَابِیْ بِكَ\nBE-ABEE ANTA WA UMMEE LAQAD A’ZOMA MOSAABEE BEKA \nMy father and mother be sacrificed for you, great is my sorrow for you.\nفَاَسْئَلُ اللهَ الَّذِیْ اَکْرَمَ مَقَامَكَ\nFA-ASALUL LAAHAL LAZEE AKRAMA MAQAAMAKA \nI pray to Allah who has honoured your status, \nوَ اَکْرَمَنِیْ بِكَ اَنْ یَرْزُقَنِیْ طَلَبَ ثَارِكَ\nWA AKRAMANEE BEKA AYN YARZOQANEE TALABA SAAREKA \nand honoured me through you, to grant me an opportunity\nمَعَ اِمَامٍ مَنْصُوْرٍ مِنْ اَهْلِ بَیْتِ مُحَمَّدٍ\nMA-A’ EMAAMIN MANSOORIN MIN AHLE BAYTE MOHAMMADIN \nto be with a victorious Imam, from the family of Muhammad, \nصَلَّی اللهُ عَلَیْہِ وَ آلِہٖ\nSALLAL LAAHO A’LAYHE WA AALEHI\nblessings of Allah be on him and his family.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اجْعَلْنِیْ عِنْدَكَ وَجِیْہًا بِالْحُسَیْنِ\nALLAAHUMMAJ A’LNEE I’NDAKA WAJEEHAN BIL-HUSAYNE \nO Allah, make me worthy of respect with You, through Husayn, \nعَلَیْہِ السَّلَامُ فِیْ الدُّنْیَا وَ اْلآخِرَۃِ\nA’LAYHIS SALAAMO FID-DUNYAA WAL AAAKHERATE \npeace be on him, in this world and the Hereafter.\nیَا اَبَا عَبْدِ اللهِ\nYAA ABAA A’BDIL LAAHE \nO Abu Abdillah, \nاِنِّی اَتَقَرَّبُ اِلَی اللهِ\nINNEE ATAQARRABO ELAL LAAHE \nI seek nearness to Allah,\nوَ اِلٰی رَسُوْلِہٖ وَ اِلٰی اَمْیرِ الْمُؤْمِنِیْنَ\nWA ELAA RASOOLEHEE WA ELAA AMEERIL MOMENEENA \nand to His Messenger, to the Commander of the Faithful,\nوَ اِلٰی فَاطِمَۃَ وَ اِلَی الْحَسَنِ وَ اِلَیْكَ\nWA ELAA FAATEMATA WA ELAL HASANE WA ELAYKA \nto Fatima, and to Hasan, and to you, \nبِمُوَالَاتِكَ وَ بِالْبَرَآئَۃِ مِمَّنْ قَاتَلَكَ وَ نَصَبَ لَک الْحَرْبَ \nBE-MAWAALAATEKA WA BIL-BARAA-ATE MIMMAN QAATALAKA WA NASABA LAKAL HARBA \nthrough love for you, and disassociating with those who killed you, and prepared to fight you\nوَ بِالْبَرَآئَۃِ مِمَّنْ اَسَّسَ اَسَاسَ الظُّلْمِ وَالْجَوْرِ عَلَیْکُمْ \nWA BIL-BARAAA-ATE MIMMAN ASSASA ASAASAZ ZULME WAL JAWRE A’LAYKUM \nand those who established the foundations of tyranny, and wrongs against you (O Ahl al-Bayt).\nوَاَبْرَءُ اِلَی اللهِ وَ اِلٰی رَسُوْلِہٖ مِمَّنْ اَسَّسَ اَسَاسَ ذٰلِكَ وَبَنی عَلَیْہِ بُنْیَانَہٗ\nWA ABRAO ELAL LAAHE WA ELAA RASOOLEHEE MIMMAN ASSASA ASAASA ZAALEKA WA BANAA A’LAYHE BUNYAANAHU \nI turn to Allah, and His Messenger, disassociating with those who laid grounds for it, and those who built upon it,\nوَ جَرٰی فِیْ ظُلْمِہٖ وَ جَوْرِہٖ عَلَیْکُمْ\nWA JARAA FEE ZULMEHEE WA JAWREHI A’LAYKUM \nand carried out oppression and cruelty, on you \nوَ عَلی اَشْیَاعِکُمْ بَرِئْتُ اِلَی اللهِ وَ اِلَیْکُمْ مِنْہُمْ\nWA A’LAA ASHYAA-E’KUM BAREA’TO ELAL LAAHE WA ELAYKUM MINHUM \nand your followers. I disassociate myself from them,\nوَ اَتَقَرَّبُ اِلَی اللهِ ثُمَّ اِلَیْکُمْ\nWA ATAQARRABO ELAL LAAHE SUMMA ELAYKUM \nand seek nearness to Allah, and then to you \nبِمُوَالَاتِکُمْ وَ مُوَالَاۃِ وَ لِیِّکُمْ\nBE-MAWAALAATEKUM WA MOWAALAATE WALIYYEKUM \nthrough love for you and your friends,\nوَ بِالْبَرَآئَۃِ مِنْ اَعْدَائِکُمْ\nWA BIL-BARAAA-ATE MIN AA’-DAAA-EKUM \nand disassociation with your enemies, \nوَ النَّاصِبِیْنَ لَکُمُ الْحَرْبَ\nWAN NAASEBEENA LAKOMUL HARBA \nand from those who went to war with you,\nوَ بِالْبَرَائَۃِ مِنْ اَشْیَاعِہِمْ وَ اَتْبَاعِہِمْ\nWA BIL BARAAA-ATE MIN ASHYAA-E’HIM WA ATBAA-E’HIM \ntheir adherents and their followers.\nاِنِّی سِلْمٌ لِمَنْ سَالَمَکُمْ\nINNEE SILMUN LEMAN SAALAMAKUM \nI am at peace with those who made peace with you, \nوَ حَرْبٌ لِمَنْ حَارَبَکُمْ\nWA HARBUN LEMAN HAARABAKUM \nand I am at war with those who went to war with you.\nوَ وَلِیٌّ لِمَنْ وَالَاکُمْ\nWA WALIYYUN LEMAN WAALAAKUM \nI befriend those who befriended you, \nوَ عَدُوٌّ لِمَنْ عَادَاکُمْ\nWA A’DUWWUN LEMAN A’ADAAKUM \nand I am at enmity with those who were your enemies.\nفَاَسْئَلُ اللهَ الَّذِیْ اَکْرَمَنِیْ بِمَعْرِفَتِکُمْ\nFA-AS-ALUL LAAHAL LAZEE AKRAMANEE BE MAA’REFATEKUM \nI pray to Allah, who has honored me with awareness of you,\nوَ مَعْرِفَۃِ اَوْلِیَآئِکُمْ\nWA MAA’REFATE AWLEYAAAEKUM \nand awareness of your friends\nوَ رَزَقَنِیَ الْبَرَآئَۃَ مِنْ اَعْدَآئِکُمْ\nWA RAZAQANIL BARAAA-ATA MIN AA’-DAAA-EKUM \nand has enabled me to withdraw from your enemies.\nاَنْ یَجْعَلَنِیْ مَعَکُمْ فِیْ الدُّنْیَا وَ اْلآخِرَۃِ\nWA ANY YAJ-A’LANEE MA-A’KUM FID DUNYAA WAL AAKHERATE \n(I pray) that He may place me with you in this world and the Hereafter.\nوَ اَنْ یُثَبِّتَ لِی عِنْدَ کُمْ قَدَمَ صِدْقٍ\nWA ANY YOSABBETA LEE I’NDAKUM QADAMA SIDQIN \nAnd (I pray) that He may strengthen for me a truthful stance \nفِیْ الدُّنْیَا وَ اْلآخِرَۃِ\nFID DUNYAA WAL AAKHERATE \nin this world and the Hereafter.\nوَ اَسْئَلُہُ اَنْ یُبَلِّغَنِی الْمَقَامَ الْمَحْمُوْدَ لَکُمْ عِنْدَ اللهِ\nWA AS-ALOHU ANY YOBALLEGHANIL MAQAAMAL MAHMOODA LAKUM I’NDAL LAAHE \nAnd I pray that He may enable me to reach, your honoured station with Allah\nوَ اَنْ یَرْزُقَنِیْ طَلَبَ ثَارِیْ \nWA ANY YARZOQANEE TALABA SAAREE \nand that He may grant me the opportunity to seek victory, \nمَعَ اِمَامٍ ہُدًی ظَاہِرٍ نَاطِقٍ بِالْحَقِّ مِنْکُمْ\nMA-A’ EMAAMIN HODAN ZAAHERIN NAATEQIN BIL-HAQQE MINKUM \nalong with a rightly guided Imam from amongst you, who will surely come and speak the truth.\nوَ اَسْئَلُ اللهَ بِحَقِّکُمْ وَ بِالشَّانِ الَّذِیْ لَکُمْ عِنْدَہٗ\nWA AS-ALUL LAAHA BE-HAQQEKUM WA BISH-SHAANIL LAZEE LAKUM I’NDAHU \nI ask Allah for your sake, and by the honoured position you have with Him,\nاَنْ یُعْطِیَنِیْ بِمُصَابِیْ بِکُمْ اَفْضَلَ مَا یُعْطِیْ مُصَابًا بِمُصِیْبَتِہٖ\nANY YOA’-TEYANEE BE-MOSAABEE BEKUM AFZALA MAA YOA’-TEE MOSAABAN BE-MOSEEBATIN \nthat He grants me grief at your sorrows, more than the personal grief that troubles anyone in tragedy.\nمُصِیْبَۃً مَا اَعْظَمَہَا\nMOSEEBATAN MAA AA’-ZAMAHAA \nWhat great sorrows (you experienced)!\nوَ اَعْظَمَ رَزِیَّتَہَا فِیْ اْلاِسْلَامِ\nWA AA’-ZAMA RAZIYYATAHAA FIL ISLAAME \nHow great was your tragedy for Islam, \nوَ فِیْ جَمِیْعِ السَّمٰوَاتِ وَ اْلأَرْضِ\nWA FEE JAMEE-I’S SAMAAWAATE WAL ARZ \nand all the Heavens and the earth!\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اجْعَلْنِیْ فِیْ مَقَامِیْ هٰذَا مِمَّنْ\nALLAAHUMMAJ A’LNEE FEE MAQAAMEE HAAZAA MIMMAN \nO Allah, make me, at this moment, \nتَنَالُہٗ مِنْكَ صَلَوَاتٌ وَ رَحْمَۃٌ وَ مَغْفِرَۃٌ\nTANAALOHU MINKA SALAWAATUN WA RAHMATUN WA MAGHFERATUN \none who receives from You, blessings, mercy, and forgiveness.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اجْعَلْ مَحْیَایَ مَحْیَا مُحَمَّدٍ وَ آلِ مُحَمَّدٍ\nALLAAHUMAJ-A'L MAHYAAYA MAHYAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN \nO Allah make me live the life of Muhammad (s.a.w.a.) and his family\nوَ مَمَاتِیْ مَمَاتَ مُحَمَّدٍ وَ آلِ مُحَمَّدٍ\nWA MAMAATEE MAMAATA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN \nand make me die the death of Muhammad (s.a.w.a.) and his family.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنَّ هٰذَا یَوْمٌ تَبَرَّكَتْ بِہٖ بَنُوْ اُمَیَّۃَ\nALLAAHUMMA INNA HAAZAA YAWMUN TABARRAKAT BEHI BANOO UMAYYATA \nO my Allah this day is a day of rejoicing for the Bani Umayyah, \nوَابْنُ آکِلَۃِ الْأَکُبَادِ اللَّعِیْنُ ابْنُ اللَّعِیْنِ عَلٰی لِسَانِكَ\nWABNO AAKELATIL AKBAADIL LA-E'ENUBNUL LA-E'ENE A'LAA LESAANEKA \nthe herd of hardened criminals, the eternally damned and accursed group, a fact that had been made public by Thee \nوَ لِسَانِ نَبِیِّكَ صَلَّی اللهُ عَلَیْہِ وَآلِہٖ\nWA LESAANE NABIYYEKA SALLAL LAAHO A’LAYHE WA AALEHI\nand Your Prophet, blessings of Allah be on him and his family,\nفِیْ کُلِّ مَوْطِنٍ وَ مَوْقِفٍ وَ قَفَ فِیْہِ نَبِیُّكَ صَلَّی اللهُ عَلَیْہِ وَ آلِہٖ\nFEE KULLE MAWTENIN WA MAWQEFIN WAQAFA FEEHE NABIYYOKA SALLAL LAAHO A’LAYHE WA AALEHI \nWho (blessings of Allah be on him and his family), in every place and at all occasions, drew attention of people to this truism.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ الْعَنْ اَبَا سُفْیَانَ وَ مُعَاوِیَۃَ\nALLAAHUMMAAL-A'N ABAA SUFYAAN WA MO-A'AWEYATA \nO Allah, curse Abu Sufyan, Mu`awiya, \nوَ یَزِیْدَ بْنَ مُعَاوِیَۃَ\nWA YAZEEDABNA MO-A'AWEYATA \nand Yazíd son of Mu`awiya \nعَلَیْہِمْ مِنْكَ اللَّعْنَۃُ اَبَدَ الْآبِدِیْنَ\nA'LAYHIM MINKAL LA’NATO ABADAL AABEDEENA \nlet it be an everlasting curse upon them from Thee.\nوَ هٰذَا یَوْمٌ فَرِحَتْ بِہٖ آلُ زِیادٍ وَ آلُ مَرْوَانَ\nWA HAAZAA YAWMUN FAREHAT BEHI AALO ZEYAADIN WA AALO MARWAANA \nAnd this is a day when the family of Ziyad was happy, and the family of Marwan, \nبِقَتْلِہِمُ الْحُسَیْنَ صَلَوٰاتُ اللهِ عَلَیْہِ\nBE-QATLEHEMUL HUSAYNA SALAWAATUL LAAHE A'LAYHHE \nbecause of their murder of Husayn, blessings of Allah be on him.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ فَضَاعِفْ عَلَیْہِمُ الَّعْنَ مِنْكَ وَ الْعَذَابَ الْاَلِيْمَ\nALLAAHUMMA FAZAA-I’F A’LAYHEMUL LA’NA MINKA WAL A’ZAABAL ALEEMA \nO Allah, so increase the curse on them from You, and the painful punishment.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَتَقَرَّبُ اِلَیْكَ فِیْ هٰذَا الْیَوْمِ\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE ATAQARRABO ELAYKA FEE HAAZAL YAWME \nO Allah, I seek nearness to You on this day, \nوَ فِیْ مَوْقِفِیْ هٰذَا وَ اَیَّامِ حَیٰوتِیْ\nWA FEE MAWQEFEE HAAZAA WA AYYAAME HAYAATEE \nand in this position, and for the rest of my life, \nبِالْبَرَآئَۃِ مِنْہُمْ وَ اللَّعْنَۃِ عَلَیْہِمْ\nBIL-BARAAA-ATE MINHUM WAL LA’NATE A’LAYHIM\nthrough disassociating with them (the enemies) and cursing them,\nوَ بِالْمُوَالَاتِ لِنَبِیِّكَ وَ آلِ نَبِیِّكَ\nWA BIL MOWAALAATE LE-NABIYYEKA WA AALE NABIYYEKA \nand through the love of Your Prophet, \nعَلَیْہِ وَ عَلِیْہِمُ السَّلَامُ\nA’LAYHE WA A’LAYHEMUS SALAAMO.\nand his family, peace be on them.\nThen say 100 times:\nاَللّٰہُمَّ الْعَنْ اَوّلَ ظَالِمٍ ظَلَمَ حَقَّ مُحَمَّدٍ\nALLAAHUMMAL A’N AWWALA ZAALEMIN ZALAMA HAQQA MOHAMMADIN \nO Allah, curse the first tyrant who oppressed, the right of Muhammad\nوَ آلِ مُحَمَّدٍ وَ آخِرَ تَابِعٍ لَہٗ عَلٰی ذٰلِكَ\nWA AALE MOHAMMADIN WA AAKHERA TAABE-I'N LAHU A'LAA ZAALEKA \nand his family, and the next who followed him on that.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ الْعَنِ الْعِصَابَۃَ الَّتِیْ جَاہَدَتِ الْحُسَیْنَ\nALLAAHUMMAL-A'NIL E'SAABATAL LATEE JAAHADATIL HUSAYNA \nO Allah, curse the group who fought Husayn,\nوَ شَایَعَتْ وَ بایَعَتْ وَ تَابَعَتْ عَلٰی قَتْلِہٖ\nWA SHAAYA-A'T WA BAA-YA-A'T WA TAA-BA-A'T A'LAA QATLEHI\nand the group which followed and supported, and joined hands to kill him.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ الْعَنْہُمْ جَمِیْعًا\nALLAHUMMAL-A'NHUM JAMEE-A'N.\nO Allah curse them all\nThen again say 100 times:\nاَلسَّلَامُ عَلَیْكَ یَا اَبَا عَبْدِ اللهِ\nASSALAAMO A'LAYKA YAA ABAA A'BDILLAAHE \nPeace be on You O Abu Abdillah\nوَ عَلَی الْأَرْوَاحِ الَّتِیْ حَلَّتْ بِفِنَآئِكَ\nWA A'LAL ARWAAHIL LATEE HALLAT BEFENAA-EKA \nand on the souls that died with you.\nعَلَیْكَ مِنّی سَلَامُ اللهِ اَبَدًا\nA'LAYKA MINNE SALAAMUL LAAHE ABADAM \nGreetings of Peace of Allah be on you, from me, forever so long as I live \nمَا بَقِیْتُ وَ بَقِيَ اللَّیْلُ وَ النَّہَارُ\nMAA BAQEETO WA BAQEYAL LAYLO WAN NAHAARO \nand so long as the night and day remain.\nوَ لَا جَعَلَہُ اللهُ آخِرَ الْعَهْدِ مِنِّی لِزِیَارَتِکُمْ\nWA LAA JA-A'LAHUL LAAHO AAKHERAL A’HDE MINNEE LE-ZEYAARATEKUM \nMay Allah not make it my last contact of ziyarat with you.\nاَلسَّلَامُ عَلَی الْحُسَیْنِ\nASSALAAMO A'LAL HUSAYNE \nPeace be on Husayn, \nوَ عَلٰی عَلِیِّ بْنِ الْحُسَیْنِ\nWA A'LAA A'LIYYIBNIL HUSAYNE \nand on Ali the son of Husayn,\nوَ عَلٰی اَوْلادِ الْحُسَیْنِ\nWA A'LAA AWLAADIL HUSAYNE \nAnd on the children of Husayn \nوَ عَلٰی اَصْحَابِ الْحُسَیْنِ\nWA A'LAA ASHAABIL HUSAYNE\nand the companions of Husayn,\nThen say:\nاَللّٰہُمَّ خُصَّ اَنْتَ اَوَّلَ ظَالِمٍ بِاللَّعْنِ مِنِّی\nALLAAHUMMA KHUSSA ANTA AWWALA ZAALEMIN BIL-LA'NE MINNEE \nO my Allah, let the curse I call down on the head of the first tyrant stick like a leech;\nوَابْدَأْ بِہٖ اَوَّلًا\nWAB DAA BEHI AWWALAN \nand stay put for ever on the first,\nثُمَّ الثَّانِيَۃْ وَ الثَّالِثَ وَالرَّابِعْ\nSUMMAS SAANEYA WAS SAALESA WAR RAABE’\nthen the second, the third, and the fourth.\nاَللَّہُمَّ الْعَنْ یَزِیْدَ خَامِسًا\nALLAAHUMMAL-A'N YAZEEDA KHAAMESAN \nO Allah, curse the fifth one, Yazíd, \nوَ الْعَنْ عُبَیْدَ اللهِ بْنِ زِیَادٍ وَابْنَ مَرْجَانَۃَ\nWAL A'N O'BAYDAL LAAH IBNA ZEYAADIN WAB NA MARJAANAH \nand Ubaidallah bin Ziyad, Ibne Marjanah, \nوَ عُمَرَبْنَ سَعْدٍ وَ شِمْرًا\nWA O'MAR ABNA SA'DIN WA SHIMRAN \nand Umar ibne Sa’d, and Shimr, \nوَ آلَ أَبِيْ سُفْیَانَ وَ آلَ زِیَادٍ\nWA AALA ABEE SUFYAANA WA AALA ZEYAADIN \nand the family of Abu Sufyan, the family of Ziyad, \nوَ آلَ مَرْوَانَ اِلٰی یَوْمِ الْقِیَامَۃِ.\nWA AALA MARWAANA ELAA YAWMIL QEYAAMATE.\nand the family of Marwan, till the Day of Judgement\nThen go in Sajdah and say:\nاَللّٰہُمَّ لَكَ الْحَمْدُ حَمْدَ الشَّاکِرِیْنَ لَكَ عَلٰی مُصَابِہِمْ\nALLAAHUMMA LAKAL HAMDO HAMDASH SHAAKEREENA LAKA A'LAA MOSAABEHIM \nO Allah, for You is Praise, Praise of those who are thankful to You (even) during tragedy.\nاَلْحَمْدُ لِلهِ عَلٰی عَظِیْمِ رَزِیَّتِیْ\nALHAMDO LILLAAHE A'LAA A'ZEEME RAZIYYATEE \nPraise be to Allah for my intense grief\nاَللّٰہُمَّ ارْزُقْنِیْ شَفَاعَۃَ الْحُسَیْنِ یَوْمَ الْوُرُوْدِ\nALLAAHUMMAR ZUQNEE SHAFAA-A'TAL HUSAYNE YAWMAL WOROODE \nO Allah, grant me the intercession of Husayn, on the Day of appearance (before You),\nوَ ثَبِّتْ لِیْ قَدَمَ صِدْقٍ عِنْدَكَ\nWA SABBIT LEE QADAMA SIDQIN I’NDAKA \nand strengthen for me a truthful stand with You, \nمَعَ الْحُسَیْنِ وَ اَصْحَابِ الْحُسَیْنِ الَّذِیْنَ \nMA-A'L HUSAYNE WA ASHAABIL HUSAYNIL LAZEENA \nwith Husayn and the companions of Husayn,\nبَذَلُوْا مُہَجَہُمْ دُوْنَ الْحُسَیْنِ عَلَیْہِ السَّلَامُ.\nBAZALOO MOHAJAHUM DOONAL HUSAYNE A'LAYHIS SALAAMO.\nwho sacrificed everything, for Husayn, peace be on him.\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    ", 
    "title": "Ziyarat e Ashura"
}